@startuml fig-ftp-control-data
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title FTP: Control Connection vs Data Connection

participant "FTP Client" as C #FFE0B2
participant "FTP Server\nport 21 (control)" as S #C8E6C9

== CONTROL CONNECTION (persistent, port 21) ==

C -> S : TCP connect to port 21
S --> C : 220 Service ready

C -> S : USER anonymous
S --> C : 331 Password required

C -> S : PASS user@host
S --> C : 230 Login successful

C -> S : PWD
S --> C : 257 "/" is current directory

== DATA CONNECTION (ephemeral, per transfer) ==

C -> S : PASV
S --> C : 227 Entering passive mode (h1,h2,h3,h4,p1,p2)

C -[#1565C0]> S : TCP connect to data port
note right : Separate TCP connection\nused only for this transfer

C -> S : LIST
S --> C : 150 Opening data connection
S -[#1565C0]-> C : <directory listing bytes>
S --> C : 226 Transfer complete
note right : Data connection closed\nafter transfer completes

C -> S : QUIT
S --> C : 221 Goodbye

legend right
  The control channel (port 21) carries
  text commands and numeric responses.
  The data channel is a separate TCP
  connection opened per transfer (LIST,
  RETR or STOR) and closed afterwards.
  This dual-channel design is unique to FTP.
endlegend
@enduml
